MODULE
  bitmap - Loading of Bitmap Data

INTRODUCTION
  This module provides functions for loading bitmap data.

INTERFACE
  loadRGB, loadRGBA
<!-- BEGIN-FUNC loadRGB -->
NAME
  bitmap::loadRGB -- load color image data

SYNOPSIS
  bitmap::loadRGB(fnam)

PARAMETER
  fnam - The name of the file to load as a string.

DESCRIPTION
  This function reads the image with filename "fnam" and
  returns a nested list of RGB values.  The image may have
  one of the formats BMP, GIF, JPG, JPEG, PNG, PBM, PGM,
  PNM, PPM, TIF, TIFF, XBM or XPM.

SEE ALSO
  bitmap::loadRGBA
<!-- END-FUNC -->
<!-- BEGIN-FUNC loadRGBA -->
NAME
  bitmap::loadRGBA -- load color image data with alpha channel

SYNOPSIS
  bitmap::loadRGBA(fnam)

PARAMETER
  fnam - The name of the file to load as a string.

DESCRIPTION
  This function reads the image with filename "fnam" and
  returns a nested list of RGBA values.  The image may have
  one of the formats BMP, GIF, JPG, JPEG, PNG, PBM, PGM, PNM,
  PPM, TIF, TIFF, XBM or XPM.  Most of these formats do not
  support an alpha channel, though.  In this case, all alpha
  values in the returned list will be 1.0.

SEE ALSO
  bitmap::loadRGB
<!-- END-FUNC -->
